<subSubSection id="49FAAF8696D1978154C378EBC895760A" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" type="comments">
<paragraph id="ACFF333E28C5B87D53EEE10005C5FE64" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="42E4282C6BAA9EE961DBB70D2EBB14B6" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName id="7AD50343BBB932D9F0D7242EEAA195A6" authorityName="Moldenke" authorityYear="1951" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Syngonanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="weddellii">
<emphasis id="3A774CFEDF844AC812F4ED40FD2A6F40" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Syngonanthus weddellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis id="1B32200BA133451708C671C1A680A1CA" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">gracilis</emphasis>
Moldenke was misplaced in 
<taxonomicName id="18045F4A87E902199D67E507A0AED34E" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Syngonanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5786F65345075DEAAAE68585BC4934B6" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Syngonanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as this taxon has truly free petals on the pistillate flower and bifid stigmatic branches. It is therefore transferred at the species level to 
<taxonomicName id="BA03488CB019B4B72B44209F0B1EAA2E" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DA13BA0F4E1D0DF96D7E62A060CDBCA" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a genus encompassing such morphological traits. The epithet 
<emphasis id="D5A22A3274B152B977F74AEB91254F39" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">gracilis</emphasis>
,however, has been previously used in 
<taxonomicName id="6A321308E6059B1EEABA4A9ECFA395D3" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6B023C8A5EE499AEC1D3DA9BC8D47284" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EC128E9198070A061A7C9DED0978F4C9" author="Koernicke, F" editor="Martius, KFP" journalOrPublisher="Typographia Regia, Muenchen" pageId="4" pageNumber="11" pagination="312 - 320" refId="B2" refString="Koernicke, F, 1863. Eriocaulaceae. In: Martius, KFP, Eichler, AW, Eds., Flora Brasiliensis 3(1). Typographia Regia, Muenchen: 312 - 320" title="Eriocaulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Brasiliensis 3 (1)." year="1863">Koernicke (1863)</bibRefCitation>
. Thus, since it is not available, we propose the new name 
<taxonomicName id="AB02E0EB54714B4ED8C7E6CA593A939B" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="rectifolius">
<emphasis id="99041885DEAAD40F38258FDABCBBA979" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus rectifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, referring to straight and ascending leaves, which differ the species from the most similar ones. 
<taxonomicName id="BFECA2F4CA7F3ABC6ED047EEB89D9D94" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="rectifolius">
<emphasis id="2F43F50AF5FD3FFE18FE892CBC85BD49" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus rectifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the type specimens collected in the mountains east of 
<normalizedToken id="1004FC1744376574421E2EF08E5A81D8" originalValue="Pirenópolis">Pirenopolis</normalizedToken>
, in the Serra dos Pirineus, 
<normalizedToken id="9533248F2E6D1E11FF303951B08D431A" originalValue="Goiás">Goias</normalizedToken>
, Brazil (
<figureCitation id="CA75E5CE744FC12BE1BACCC01C19A65B" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Paepalanthus rectifolius Trovo, Echter &amp; Sano distribution map." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10035" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). During our research on 
<taxonomicName id="9BBA85E978DA30153EF2BDE77D27002D" genus="Eriocaulaceae" lsidName="" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" rank="genus">Eriocaulaceae</taxonomicName>
systematics, we studied collections from several herbaria (B, BHCB, BM, BR, BRLU, C, CESJ, ESA, ESALQ, F, G, HUEFS, INPA, K, L, LE, LL, M, MO, NY, OUPR, OXF, P, R, RB, S, SP, SPF, UEC and UPS; acronyms in 
<bibRefCitation id="D6E92EE1F57C3F60D039F47B130A341A" author="Thiers, B" journalOrPublisher="Springer - Verlag, Berlin" pageId="4" pageNumber="11" publicationUrl="http://sciweb.nybg.org/science2/IndexHerbariorum.asp" refId="B8" refString="Thiers, B, continuously updated. Index herbariorum: a global directory of public herbaria and associated staff. New York Botanical Garden's Virtual Herbarium., http://sciweb.nybg.org/science2/IndexHerbariorum.asp" title="Index herbariorum: a global directory of public herbaria and associated staff. New York Botanical Garden's Virtual Herbarium" url="http://sciweb.nybg.org/science2/IndexHerbariorum.asp" year="continuously updated">Thiers continuously updated</bibRefCitation>
). However, despite the presence of several collections from the Serra dos Pirineus, we did not find other specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="44AEED650F9B28F5743DF78967558525" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="rectifolius">
<emphasis id="B0BBFD66E4F8B574D3CA9541FBF2C8C5" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus rectifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
besides the type. Individuals with immature as well as old inflorescences were collected in January.
</paragraph>
<caption id="9C012CFF4ED58C376BAB466314A0A5D1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10035" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="9E33209E3E42F0D7476C88B63F2720AB" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="A7F6813D56DFDC8E32EAFC484755B148" bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Figure 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8301CD0BA322AB73BF127A5499B29D59" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="rectifolius">
<emphasis id="5A4D757A17658613EB8C2E4797EE0538" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus rectifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="35BD488A3B534047E4AACAF97956CEA9" originalValue="Trovó">Trovo</normalizedToken>
, Echter &amp; Sano distribution map.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="C0A545993EB70322CED4491DC0AE8DD7" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
The morphologically related species are 
<taxonomicName id="7CC630266CA9100323EAFEDE282F6ECC" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Bong." class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="flaccidus">
<emphasis id="C0184F373099F5FFAF7AD7951C3F7C39" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus flaccidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bong.) Koern. (1863), 
<taxonomicName id="D59E902D95F7360771FD5D63B07BE2A2" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="trichophyllus">
<emphasis id="5D6FA660C5CB8D2F80CEA32180CB0448" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus trichophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bong.) Koern. (1863), and 
<taxonomicName id="4453097020C3A1372F11CBADAB9080AC" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="strictus">
<emphasis id="484B44499B871037F35EC753BFE3515C" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus strictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Koern. (1863), three species with dimerous flowers recently excluded from 
<taxonomicName id="A2D34A0D844A0CAA1FD55DA18C08E5FC" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D7B48C4860ECA2159AF380AD64A0F450" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="58E7C25974B5B22E9A43CD394017C2EA" genus="Diphyomene" lsidName="" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8920A5677B045BEF4CE80FAEAA56389C" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Diphyomene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ruhland (1903) (
<bibRefCitation id="88285534B11059488587CA9DAD324D0A" author="Trovo, M" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="4" pageNumber="11" pagination="49 - 55" refId="B9" refString="Trovo, M, Sano, PT, 2010. Taxonomic survey of Paepalanthus sect. Diphyomene Ruhland (Eriocaulaceae). Phytotaxa 14: 49 - 55" title="Taxonomic survey of Paepalanthus sect. Diphyomene Ruhland (Eriocaulaceae)." volume="14" year="2010">
<normalizedToken id="888FD980A86A4EFD8D78E6B84E5AB0E9" originalValue="Trovó">Trovo</normalizedToken>
and Sano 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). As mentioned above, 
<taxonomicName id="CA3F784FB66C7B0B1DA774412EAD3C7E" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="rectifolius">
<emphasis id="30C147ECEC0FBA4AE3F95E2097F89A31" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus rectifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from these three species by its ascending and straight leaves (vs. recurved). It is easily differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="C76FEDA143213E63E997FC99AEF2E3CA" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="strictus">
<emphasis id="BC20D8E7A167E98F256030D458BBBE9D" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus strictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="19170951AC1844721A3E107BDC1E51A2" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="trichophyllus">
<emphasis id="72E6F466BF09883CAA8ECA29DC725C50" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus trichophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its linear leaves (vs. lanceolate), golden involucral bracts (vs. dark castaneous), and linear floral bracts (vs. oblong). 
<taxonomicName id="87B0E4662BEC67CF798E1D3498663D98" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Bong." class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="flaccidus">
<emphasis id="F43C3D2EE8EAC13F6AF4D44C60C89A9B" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus flaccidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most similar species, due to the linear leaves, to the golden involucral bracts, whose internal series might also be tufted in the apex, and to the villous pubescence, with long pedicellate trichomes. Both may be considered sympatric as they are reported to 
<normalizedToken id="28832CD51AE233C045AA776E67AB067A" originalValue="Goiás">Goias</normalizedToken>
and occur in the same habitats. 
<taxonomicName id="50931E1D4D677CE6DB31AD0E18258338" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="rectifolius">
<emphasis id="13385B89E428F57F10CC5E3664FD2366" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus rectifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="ACC7E3FB28A01A205A7F41D8D8C8CE2C" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Bong." class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="flaccidus">
<emphasis id="9805535A70BBC082F94B1E91B83E9D33" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Paepalanthus flaccidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its much longer leaves (2.0-4.0 cm vs. 0.5-1.5 cm), linear floral bracts (vs. oblong), and staminate flowers without lobes (vs. markedly lobed).
</paragraph>
